      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WALL STREET GIRL (4) drew wide and was outclassed when tackling a G3 for the mares last start so will relish both a class drop and a better barrier. Came from the back row to win at Pinjarra prior so can bounce back. MAJOR DISCO (6) raced wide and missed narrowly fresh then led from this barrier and dug deep to get home by a narrow margin at Bunbury last week. Steps up a level but he is going well enough enough to cope. MADDY ROCKS (3) is heading the right way, coming from the back row to place in her last two attempts at this circuit and distance. Aided by a better draw. HENRIK LARSSON NZ (7) should be at his peak for this. Drops in grade on the last attempt did a good job to come from a 30m handicap and place two back at Pinjarra.",
